  "prompt": "What are some cultural faux pas among actors?",
  "response": "Here are some cultural faux pas or unwritten rules in the acting world:\n\n1. Upstaging (deliberately drawing attention away from other actors)\n2. Not knowing or respecting your lines during rehearsals\n3. Being unprofessional or difficult on set\n4. Showing up late or unprepared\n5. Criticizing other actors publicly\n6. Breaking concentration during a scene\n7. Refusing to take direction from the director\n8. Not being supportive of fellow cast members\n9. Talking about a project before it's officially announced\n10. Revealing spoilers about a production\n11. Not respecting technical crew members\n12. Being overly competitive with other actors\n13. Discussing salary or contract details publicly\n14. Not maintaining professional boundaries\n15. Refusing to do certain types of scenes without prior discussion\n\nThese are general guidelines, and specific norms can vary depending on the production, genre, and cultural context.",
